124,134,137,144,153,161,173]},"ep_plan_001":{"taskId":"260409-111824","episodeId":"ep_plan_001","source":"plan","content":"Task: 260409-111824 | Outcome: completed | Observation: Task 260409-111824 successfully created an isOdd utility function in src/utils/math.ts with all 7 pipeline stages completing in 212 seconds and zero retries across all stages. However, the verify stage reported FAIL with typecheck errors in .next/dev/types/validator.ts (TS2344 type constraint failures on modal and ErrorPage.test imports), yet the ship stage proceeded to completion without blocking. This run exhibits the same verify-then-ship pattern failure documented in retrospectives for runs 832 and 841, where verification failures do not prevent pipeline progression to the ship stage. | Pattern: This is the third consecutive instance of the identical pattern (runs 832, 841, and now 260409-111824) where verify-stage typecheck failures fail to block deployment. The previous two retrospectives both recommended adding a conditional gate in ship to check verify exit status, but the flaw persists unchanged, indicating the recommendation was not implemented. | Suggestion: Implement the conditional gate in the ship stage that was recommended in the two prior retrospectives: check verify stage exit status and halt with a clear error message when verify reports FAIL, rather than proceeding silently to ship. | Flaw: verify — Verify stage FAIL status does not prevent pipeline progression to ship stage | Stages: taskify:completed, plan:completed, build:completed, verify:completed, review:completed, review-fix:completed, ship:completed","createdAt":"2026-04-09T08:22:29.692Z","wordCount":1505,"positions":[0,6,13,22,31,43,56,61,68,75,88,99,105,113,125,129,135,140,154,163,170,184,188,200,205,213,224,232,245,252,258,267,277,287,298,303,307,313,323,327,334,339,350,362,372,382,387,397,405,410,416,429,440,448,463,467,480,485,497,502,510,518,532,551,556,564,575,588,600,604,612,621,640,645,654,675,681,693,709